Joburg Central Cluster Police stations began the crime fighting operations on Friday wrapping up this morning. JOHANNESBURG â€“ Gauteng police say a total of 161 suspects have been arrested in Johannesburg central and surrounding areas for various offences this weekend. Joburg Central Cluster Police stations began the crime fighting operations on Friday wrapping up this morning. At least forty of the arrests were for drunk driving. In the Western Cape three people have died on the roads over the weekend. Twenty-nine people have been arrested on the roads since the start of the weekend as they have been found to be under the influence. Fines to the value of four hundred and nine thousand rand have been issued.